Many people in England don't know the Leipzig team, otherwise they wouldn't let Mourinho tell such fairy tales: Kane and Son were missing ...
The top 3 players from Leipzig in recent years were Werner, Poulsen and Forsberg. Poulsen and Forsberg came on in the 77th and 83rd minute, which means that they did not play for most of the game because they were not physically fit. When both are in full possession of their powers, Leipzig is much stronger than they are at the moment.

Poulsen and Forsberg have the same value for Leipzig as Kane and Son for Tottenham.

Also note the following name: Julian Nagelsmann.
You don't know who Nagelsmann is? Do you know Jürgen Klopp? He is team manager in Liverpool.

Ask the people in Liverpool, they can tell you a little bit about Klopp. He's really not bad.

And Nagelsmann is the new Klopp.
He has only been team manager in Leipzig this season and has done a great job.

Leipzig is currently number 2 in Germany after Bayern Munich and before Dortmund.

He will be even more successful in Leipzig than he was with Hoffenheim before.

snippet.textDisplay:
I'm a Spurs fan and I just don't get it. What should he do? Say that it's business as usual, Spurs are going to challenge for all trophies this season, etc? Why is it bad to recognise that it's the worst possible situation for the team and start building from there? Would it be better to tell lies?

Also, something I doubt many noticed, when he said in the interview "Imagine Liverpool playing without Salah, Mane and Firmino, or Barca without Griezmann, Messi and Suarez", this was a reference not only to Son and Harry, but also to Eriksen.

The team really is at a crossroads. Yesterday i suddenly realised that it's an almost entirely different squad than the one it was this time last year. And since the new additions are young players who just arrived from abroad, it wouldn't make any sense to me if someone said something different from what Jose said.
